<topic id="xml-transformation-with-xquery">
  <title>XML Transformation with XQuery</title>
  <!--Proofed-->
  <body>
    <p>Use the <uicontrol>XML transformation with XQuery</uicontrol> scenario to apply a
      transformation in which an XQuery file queries an XML file for the output results. </p>
    <p>To create an <uicontrol>XML transformation with XQuery</uicontrol> scenario, use one of the
      following methods:<ul id="ul_zwx_pg5_3r">
        <li>Go to <menucascade>
            <uicontrol>Window</uicontrol>
            <uicontrol>Show View</uicontrol>
          </menucascade> and select <uicontrol><image href="../img/TransformConfig16.png"
              id="image_edz_rvv_sr"/>Transformation Scenarios</uicontrol> to display this view.
          Click the <uicontrol>New</uicontrol> button and select <uicontrol>XML transformation with
            XQuery</uicontrol>.</li>
        <li>Use the <uicontrol><image href="../img/TransformConfig16.png" id="image_yqd_svv_sr"
            />Configure Transformation Scenario(s) (<shortcut
              conref="oxygen-shortcuts-list.dita#oxygen-shortcuts-list/shortcut_ctrl_shift_c"
              product="author developer editor"/><shortcut
              conref="oxygen-shortcuts-list.dita#oxygen-shortcuts-list/alt_shift_tc_shortcut"
              product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse"/>)</uicontrol> action from the
            <uicontrol>Transformation</uicontrol> toolbar or the <menucascade
            product="author developer editor">
            <uicontrol>Document</uicontrol>
            <uicontrol> Transformation</uicontrol>
          </menucascade><uicontrol product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse"
            >XML</uicontrol> menu. Then click the <uicontrol>New</uicontrol> button and select
            <uicontrol>XML transformation with XQuery</uicontrol>.</li>
        <li>Use the <uicontrol><image href="../img/ApplyStyleSheet16.png" id="image_utw_2xs_1r"
            />Apply Transformation Scenario(s) (<shortcut
              conref="oxygen-shortcuts-list.dita#oxygen-shortcuts-list/ctrl-shift-t-shortcut"
              product="author developer editor"/><shortcut
              conref="oxygen-shortcuts-list.dita#oxygen-shortcuts-list/alt_shift_tt_shortcut"
              product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse"/>)</uicontrol> action from the
            <uicontrol>Transformation</uicontrol> toolbar or the <menucascade
            product="author developer editor">
            <uicontrol>Document</uicontrol>
            <uicontrol> Transformation</uicontrol>
          </menucascade><uicontrol product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse"
            >XML</uicontrol> menu. Then click the <uicontrol>New</uicontrol> button and select
            <uicontrol>XML transformation with XQuery</uicontrol>.<note
            conref="xml-transformation-with-xslt.dita#xml-transformation-with-xslt/note-001"/></li>
      </ul></p>
    <p>All three methods open the <uicontrol>New Scenario</uicontrol> dialog box. This dialog allows
      you to configure the options that control the transformation.</p>
    <p conref="xml-transformation-with-xslt.dita#xml-transformation-with-xslt/name-storage-options"/>
    <p>The <ph product="author developer editor">lower part of the </ph>dialog box contains the
      following tabs:<ul>
        <li><xref href="the-xquery-tab.dita#the-xquery-tab"
          ><uicontrol>XQuery</uicontrol></xref>.</li>
        <li><xref href="fo-processor-tab--xml-xquery.dita#fo-processor-tab--xml-xquery"
              ><uicontrol>FO Processor</uicontrol></xref>.</li>
        <li><xref href="output-xml-xquery.dita#output-xml-xquery"
            ><uicontrol>Output</uicontrol></xref>.</li>
      </ul></p>
  </body>
